### Django REST API Testing
### Replace the old FastAPI with Django REST Framework

### Health Check
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/health/

### Get all branches (previously missing in FastAPI)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/branches/

### Get specific branch
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/branches/1/

### Get all vaccines
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/vaccines/

### Get specific vaccine
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/vaccines/1/

### Get all users
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/users/

### Create a new user
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/users/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "testuser",
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "first_name": "Test",
    "last_name": "User",
    "password": "testpass123"
}

### Get all appointments
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/appointments/

### Create an appointment
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/appointments/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "user": 1,
    "vaccine": 1,
    "branch": 1,
    "datetime": "2025-10-20T10:00:00Z",
    "notes": "Regular appointment"
}

### Get all doses
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/doses/

### Create a dose record
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/doses/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "vaccine": 1,
    "user": 1,
    "date_administered": "2025-10-14",
    "dose_number": 1
}

### Update an appointment
PATCH http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/appointments/1/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "completed"
}

### Delete an appointment
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/appointments/1/
